      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Product Design interviews evaluate your design process, problem-solving approach, and ability to advocate for users while balancing business constraints. Your portfolio is central, but whiteboard challenges and critique sessions are equally important."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Design thinking and process\n- User empathy and research skills\n- Visual and interaction design craft\n- Collaboration with engineers and PMs\n- Ability to receive and give critique"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical design interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Portfolio review** (45-60 min) - Deep dive into 2-3 projects\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-6 hours):\n   - Whiteboard/app critique challenge\n   - Design exercise (take-home or live)\n   - Cross-functional collaboration round\n   - Behavioral/values round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "In portfolio reviews, focus on the WHY behind design decisions, not just the final UI. Process matters more than polish."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
